Title 
Design and Setup of a Social Media Advertising Campaign on Instagram 


Aim 
To understand and configure an Instagram advertising campaign by boosting posts 
directly from Instagram and by using Meta Business tools, including campaign 
objectives, audience targeting, budget planning, ad creatives, placements, and 
performance metrics. 
Objectives 
1.
 
To understand the prerequisites for advertising on Instagram 
2.
 
To differentiate between boosted posts and Ads Manager–based campaigns 
3.
 
To define campaign objectives aligned with marketing goals 
4.
 
To configure audience targeting parameters 
5.
 
To set budget and campaign duration 
6.
 
To understand ad placements and creative formats 
7.
 
To study ad performance metrics and tracking



Theory 
Instagram Advertising Overview 
Instagram advertising allows businesses to promote content to a wider audience 
beyond their followers. Ads can appear in: 
● 
Feed 
● 
Stories 
● 
Reels 
● 
Explore section 
Instagram ads support various objectives such as brand awareness, profile visits, 
website traffic, and messages. 
Ways to Advertise on Instagram 
1.
 
Boosting Posts Directly from Instagram (Limited Features) 
2.
 
Advertising via Meta Business Suite / Ads Manager (Advanced Control) 
Boosted Post vs Dark Post 
● 
BoostedPost:
 
An existing organic Instagram post promoted using advertising budget. Visible 
on the profile. 
 
● 
DarkPost:
 
An ad created solely for advertising. Not visible on the Instagram profile. The 
choice depends on compaign goals.


Prerequisites 
1. 
Instagram account must be switched to Professional (Business or Creator)
 
2.
 
Profile must comply with Instagram advertising policies 
3.
 
Payment method required only at final publish stage 
A Facebook Page is recommended for Ads Manager–based campaigns but not 
mandatory for basic boosting from the Instagram app.









Result 
An Instagram advertising campaign was successfully designed using both in-app 
promotion and Meta Business tools. Campaign objectives, audience targeting, budget 
allocation, placements, and performance metrics were clearly understood and 
configured.

